WEBVTT

00:00:00.160 --> 00:00:03.120
4-3-3. The 4-3-3 is one of the most common

00:00:03.120 --> 00:00:04.640
shapes in football. It uses four

00:00:04.640 --> 00:00:06.799
defenders, three midfielders, and three

00:00:06.799 --> 00:00:08.480
attackers. The midfield three usually

00:00:08.480 --> 00:00:10.000
sit as one holding player with two

00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:11.519
slightly ahead, giving balance.

00:00:11.519 --> 00:00:13.120
Defensively, it's solid because the

00:00:13.120 --> 00:00:14.719
midfield protects the back four and the

00:00:14.719 --> 00:00:16.160
wide forwards can track back to help

00:00:16.160 --> 00:00:17.680
fullbacks. In attack, it's very

00:00:17.680 --> 00:00:19.439
flexible. The wingers stretch the pitch,

00:00:19.439 --> 00:00:20.960
the striker stay central, and the

00:00:20.960 --> 00:00:22.640
midfield can control possession. It's a

00:00:22.640 --> 00:00:24.080
formation built for both pressing and

00:00:24.080 --> 00:00:25.519
attacking football. Legendary teams like

00:00:25.519 --> 00:00:27.119
Guadiola's Barcelona and Klopp's

00:00:27.119 --> 00:00:29.119
Liverpool made the 4-3-3 famous by

00:00:29.119 --> 00:00:31.439
dominating games with it. The 4-2-3-1 is

00:00:31.439 --> 00:00:33.040
another modern favorite. It has four

00:00:33.040 --> 00:00:34.960
defenders, two holding midfielders just

00:00:34.960 --> 00:00:36.239
in front of them, three attacking

00:00:36.239 --> 00:00:38.480
midfielders, and one striker. The key is

00:00:38.480 --> 00:00:40.079
the double pivot. Those two deeper

00:00:40.079 --> 00:00:41.840
midfielders protect the defense and stop

00:00:41.840 --> 00:00:43.760
counterattacks. Defensively, this makes

00:00:43.760 --> 00:00:45.360
the team very hard to break through in

00:00:45.360 --> 00:00:46.879
the middle. In attack, the three behind

00:00:46.879 --> 00:00:48.480
the striker, usually two wide players

00:00:48.480 --> 00:00:50.160
and a number 10, create plenty of

00:00:50.160 --> 00:00:51.520
chances while supporting the lone

00:00:51.520 --> 00:00:53.120
forward. It's balanced, flexible, and

00:00:53.120 --> 00:00:54.239
can adapt to pressing or

00:00:54.239 --> 00:00:56.000
counterattacking styles. That's why many

00:00:56.000 --> 00:00:57.520
top clubs in Europe use it as their

00:00:57.520 --> 00:01:00.160
go-to system. The 4-4-2 is the classic

00:01:00.160 --> 00:01:02.000
formation that dominated football for

00:01:02.000 --> 00:01:03.920
decades. It's made of four defenders,

00:01:03.920 --> 00:01:05.600
four midfielders in a straight line, and

00:01:05.600 --> 00:01:07.680
two strikers. Defensively, it's very

00:01:07.680 --> 00:01:09.600
organized with two banks of four sitting

00:01:09.600 --> 00:01:11.360
close together, leaving little space for

00:01:11.360 --> 00:01:13.200
opponents. Attacking wise, having two

00:01:13.200 --> 00:01:14.799
strikers up top gives plenty of goal

00:01:14.799 --> 00:01:16.320
threat with midfielders supporting from

00:01:16.320 --> 00:01:18.320
wide areas. It's simple, easy to

00:01:18.320 --> 00:01:19.520
understand, and doesn't require

00:01:19.520 --> 00:01:21.119
complicated tactics, which is why it

00:01:21.119 --> 00:01:22.880
became so popular worldwide. While less

00:01:22.880 --> 00:01:24.400
common today at the elite level, it was

00:01:24.400 --> 00:01:25.920
the foundation of many great teams like

00:01:25.920 --> 00:01:27.840
Sir Alex Ferguson's Manchester United in

00:01:27.840 --> 00:01:30.799
the 1990s. The 4-1-2-1-2 is a narrower

00:01:30.799 --> 00:01:33.280
version of the classic 4-4-2. It has four

00:01:33.280 --> 00:01:35.119
defenders, a defensive midfielder at the

00:01:35.119 --> 00:01:36.960
base, two central midfielders, and an

00:01:36.960 --> 00:01:38.320
attacking midfielder behind two

00:01:38.320 --> 00:01:40.400
strikers. Defensively, the holding

00:01:40.400 --> 00:01:41.840
midfielder gives protection to the back

00:01:41.840 --> 00:01:43.439
four while the two central midfielders

00:01:43.439 --> 00:01:45.200
cover ground. In attack, the number 10

00:01:45.200 --> 00:01:46.799
links play with the strikers, creating

00:01:46.799 --> 00:01:48.320
chances through the middle. It's

00:01:48.320 --> 00:01:49.840
excellent for controlling central areas,

00:01:49.840 --> 00:01:51.280
but can be exposed out wide because

00:01:51.280 --> 00:01:52.799
there are no natural wingers. Teams like

00:01:52.799 --> 00:01:54.479
Anchelotti's AC Milan used it

00:01:54.479 --> 00:01:55.920
successfully to dominate the midfield

00:01:55.920 --> 00:01:59.600
battle. 4-1-4-1. The 4-1-4-1 is a compact and

00:01:59.600 --> 00:02:01.759
organized system. It has four defenders,

00:02:01.759 --> 00:02:03.439
a single holding midfielder sitting in

00:02:03.439 --> 00:02:05.040
front of them, four midfielders ahead,

00:02:05.040 --> 00:02:07.200
and one striker up top. Defensively,

00:02:07.200 --> 00:02:08.800
that holding midfielder is key,

00:02:08.800 --> 00:02:10.319
shielding the back four and stopping

00:02:10.319 --> 00:02:11.920
attacks through the middle. The midfield

00:02:11.920 --> 00:02:13.520
four can drop back to form two strong

00:02:13.520 --> 00:02:15.040
banks, making the team tough to break

00:02:15.040 --> 00:02:16.800
down. In attack, the wide midfielders

00:02:16.800 --> 00:02:18.560
push forward to support the lone striker

00:02:18.560 --> 00:02:20.080
while the central players link up in

00:02:20.080 --> 00:02:21.920
possession. It's simple, stable, and

00:02:21.920 --> 00:02:23.120
works well for teams who want to

00:02:23.120 --> 00:02:24.959
frustrate opponents while keeping shape.

00:02:24.959 --> 00:02:27.760
4-5-1. The 4-5-1 is designed to pack the

00:02:27.760 --> 00:02:29.520
midfield and control space. It's built

00:02:29.520 --> 00:02:31.760
on four defenders, five midfielders, and

00:02:31.760 --> 00:02:33.840
one striker. Defensively, it's very

00:02:33.840 --> 00:02:35.680
solid with five across midfield blocking

00:02:35.680 --> 00:02:37.519
passing lanes and forcing opponents

00:02:37.519 --> 00:02:39.599
wide. In attack, the wide midfielders

00:02:39.599 --> 00:02:41.120
often push forward, turning it into a

00:02:41.120 --> 00:02:42.239
front three, while the central

00:02:42.239 --> 00:02:43.599
midfielders support from deeper

00:02:43.599 --> 00:02:45.360
positions. It's a system that values

00:02:45.360 --> 00:02:47.440
discipline and organization, often used

00:02:47.440 --> 00:02:49.040
by underdogs to frustrate stronger

00:02:49.040 --> 00:02:50.480
teams, but it also allows quick

00:02:50.480 --> 00:02:52.160
counterattacks as the wide players can

00:02:52.160 --> 00:02:53.760
break forward quickly to supply the lone

00:02:53.760 --> 00:02:56.640
striker. 4-2-2-2. The 4-2-2-2 is an

00:02:56.640 --> 00:02:58.319
interesting and aggressive shape. It

00:02:58.319 --> 00:03:00.000
uses four defenders, two holding

00:03:00.000 --> 00:03:01.840
midfielders, two attacking midfielders

00:03:01.840 --> 00:03:03.840
tucked inside, and two strikers.

00:03:03.840 --> 00:03:05.599
Defensively, the double pivot gives

00:03:05.599 --> 00:03:07.280
protection in front of the backline,

00:03:07.280 --> 00:03:08.959
making it harder for opponents to attack

00:03:08.959 --> 00:03:10.720
centrally. In attack, the two attacking

00:03:10.720 --> 00:03:12.720
midfielders operate in half spaces,

00:03:12.720 --> 00:03:14.239
linking play with the strikers and

00:03:14.239 --> 00:03:16.239
creating overloads. With two forwards up

00:03:16.239 --> 00:03:17.599
front, there's always a strong goal

00:03:17.599 --> 00:03:19.040
threat. The system is narrow, so it

00:03:19.040 --> 00:03:20.640
relies heavily on fullbacks to provide

00:03:20.640 --> 00:03:22.319
width. It's been used by Brazilian teams

00:03:22.319 --> 00:03:23.920
and the Red Bull football clubs for high

00:03:23.920 --> 00:03:27.440
pressing styles. 4-3-2-1. The 4-3-2-1, also

00:03:27.440 --> 00:03:29.040
known as the Christmas tree, has four

00:03:29.040 --> 00:03:30.879
defenders, three central midfielders,

00:03:30.879 --> 00:03:32.959
two attacking midfielders, and a lone

00:03:32.959 --> 00:03:34.959
striker. Defensively, the three central

00:03:34.959 --> 00:03:36.799
midfielders give plenty of cover, while

00:03:36.799 --> 00:03:38.319
the two attacking midfielders can drop

00:03:38.319 --> 00:03:40.159
in to make a compact block of five. In

00:03:40.159 --> 00:03:41.599
attack, the attacking midfielders play

00:03:41.599 --> 00:03:43.360
behind the striker, creating chances and

00:03:43.360 --> 00:03:45.200
linking play, while fullbacks often push

00:03:45.200 --> 00:03:46.879
forward to provide width. It's a

00:03:46.879 --> 00:03:48.319
formation designed for control in

00:03:48.319 --> 00:03:50.239
midfield, limiting space for opponents.

00:03:50.239 --> 00:03:52.480
Carlo Angelotti's AC Milan famously used

00:03:52.480 --> 00:03:54.560
it in the 2000s, combining creativity

00:03:54.560 --> 00:03:57.840
with defensive strength. 4-1-2-3. The 4-1-2-3

00:03:57.840 --> 00:04:00.319
is a modern variation of the 4-3-3. It

00:04:00.319 --> 00:04:02.000
uses four defenders, one holding

00:04:02.000 --> 00:04:03.760
midfielder sitting deep, two central

00:04:03.760 --> 00:04:05.519
midfielders, and a front three.

00:04:05.519 --> 00:04:06.959
Defensively, the single holding

00:04:06.959 --> 00:04:08.720
midfielder protects the back four,

00:04:08.720 --> 00:04:10.239
allowing the other two midfielders to

00:04:10.239 --> 00:04:11.840
press higher up the pitch. This makes it

00:04:11.840 --> 00:04:13.360
tough for opponents to build through the

00:04:13.360 --> 00:04:14.959
center. In attack, the wide forwards

00:04:14.959 --> 00:04:16.479
stretch the game, the central striker

00:04:16.479 --> 00:04:18.160
provides a focal point, and the midfield

00:04:18.160 --> 00:04:19.840
supports from behind. It's a possession

00:04:19.840 --> 00:04:21.359
heavy system that suits teams who want

00:04:21.359 --> 00:04:24.880
control and fluidity. 3-4-3. The 3-4-3 is an

00:04:24.880 --> 00:04:26.720
adventurous and modern setup. It has

00:04:26.720 --> 00:04:28.400
three center backs, four midfielders,

00:04:28.400 --> 00:04:29.680
including wing backs, and three

00:04:29.680 --> 00:04:31.680
attackers. Defensively, the wing backs

00:04:31.680 --> 00:04:33.199
drop into a back five, making it

00:04:33.199 --> 00:04:35.120
compact. In attack, those wing backs

00:04:35.120 --> 00:04:36.560
push high to provide width while the

00:04:36.560 --> 00:04:38.160
front three stretch the opposition. It's

00:04:38.160 --> 00:04:39.680
a great system for pressing because the

00:04:39.680 --> 00:04:41.199
attackers can close down quickly and

00:04:41.199 --> 00:04:42.960
force mistakes. It suits teams who want

00:04:42.960 --> 00:04:44.479
to control possession while still being

00:04:44.479 --> 00:04:46.320
dangerous going forward. Antonio Conte's

00:04:46.320 --> 00:04:47.600
Chelsea won the Premier League with the

00:04:47.600 --> 00:04:49.759
343 and it remains popular with coaches

00:04:49.759 --> 00:04:53.199
who want flexibility. 3-5-2. The 3-5-2 has

00:04:53.199 --> 00:04:54.880
three center backs, five midfielders

00:04:54.880 --> 00:04:56.639
with wing backs on each side and two

00:04:56.639 --> 00:04:58.800
strikers. Defensively, the midfield five

00:04:58.800 --> 00:05:00.080
make it tough to play through and the

00:05:00.080 --> 00:05:01.600
wing backs track back to form a back

00:05:01.600 --> 00:05:03.360
five when needed. In attack, the wing

00:05:03.360 --> 00:05:04.880
backs push forward to provide width

00:05:04.880 --> 00:05:06.880
while the two strikers combine up front.

00:05:06.880 --> 00:05:08.320
This gives teams both attacking options

00:05:08.320 --> 00:05:10.400
and defensive stability. is particularly

00:05:10.400 --> 00:05:11.840
effective for counterattacking because

00:05:11.840 --> 00:05:13.360
of the two strikers, but it can also

00:05:13.360 --> 00:05:14.720
dominate games with strong midfield

00:05:14.720 --> 00:05:16.479
control. Contest Juventus and Inter

00:05:16.479 --> 00:05:18.720
Milan used the 3-5-2 to great success in

00:05:18.720 --> 00:05:22.160
Italy. 3-4-1-2. The 3-4-1-2 is a variation of

00:05:22.160 --> 00:05:24.960
the 352. It has three center backs, four

00:05:24.960 --> 00:05:26.800
midfielders with wing backs, one

00:05:26.800 --> 00:05:28.960
attacking midfielder, and two strikers.

00:05:28.960 --> 00:05:30.960
Defensively, the midfield four and back

00:05:30.960 --> 00:05:32.560
three create a solid block in the

00:05:32.560 --> 00:05:34.479
center. In attack, the number 10 plays

00:05:34.479 --> 00:05:36.400
behind the strikers, linking midfield to

00:05:36.400 --> 00:05:38.240
attack and creating chances. This gives

00:05:38.240 --> 00:05:40.080
the team both creativity and goal

00:05:40.080 --> 00:05:41.600
threat. It's a system that allows

00:05:41.600 --> 00:05:43.600
flexibility, solid when defending, but

00:05:43.600 --> 00:05:47.280
dangerous in attack. 3-2-4-1. The 3-2-4-1 is a

00:05:47.280 --> 00:05:48.960
very attacking system. It has three

00:05:48.960 --> 00:05:51.120
defenders, two holding midfielders, four

00:05:51.120 --> 00:05:53.520
attacking midfielders, and one striker.

00:05:53.520 --> 00:05:55.280
Defensively, the two holding players

00:05:55.280 --> 00:05:56.960
screen the back three, helping cover

00:05:56.960 --> 00:05:58.720
wide spaces when wing backs push

00:05:58.720 --> 00:06:00.320
forward. In attack, the front four

00:06:00.320 --> 00:06:02.000
overload the opposition with two wide

00:06:02.000 --> 00:06:03.440
players and two central creators

00:06:03.440 --> 00:06:05.199
supporting the striker. This shape is

00:06:05.199 --> 00:06:06.479
designed for constant pressure and

00:06:06.479 --> 00:06:08.240
possession, keeping the ball high up the

00:06:08.240 --> 00:06:10.240
pitch. Pep Guardiola has famously used

00:06:10.240 --> 00:06:11.919
this formation at Manchester City, where

00:06:11.919 --> 00:06:13.520
the aim is to dominate opponents and

00:06:13.520 --> 00:06:16.160
create chance after chance. 3-4-2-1. The

00:06:16.160 --> 00:06:18.560
3421 has three center backs, four

00:06:18.560 --> 00:06:20.160
midfielders with wing backs, two

00:06:20.160 --> 00:06:22.080
attacking midfielders, and a striker.

00:06:22.080 --> 00:06:24.000
Defensively, the wing backs drop back to

00:06:24.000 --> 00:06:25.600
create a back five, keeping the team

00:06:25.600 --> 00:06:27.440
compact. In attack, the two attacking

00:06:27.440 --> 00:06:29.199
midfielders support the striker, often

00:06:29.199 --> 00:06:30.639
drifting wide or dropping into pockets

00:06:30.639 --> 00:06:32.400
of space to create chances. It's a

00:06:32.400 --> 00:06:33.680
flexible formation that gives both

00:06:33.680 --> 00:06:35.199
defensive security and attacking

00:06:35.199 --> 00:06:36.880
numbers. Thomas Tukul used this at

00:06:36.880 --> 00:06:38.400
Chelsea with players like Mason Mount

00:06:38.400 --> 00:06:39.919
and Kai Havitz thriving as the two

00:06:39.919 --> 00:06:43.039
behind the striker. 5-3-2. The 5-3-2 has

00:06:43.039 --> 00:06:44.800
five defenders with wing backs, three

00:06:44.800 --> 00:06:46.880
central midfielders, and two strikers.

00:06:46.880 --> 00:06:48.800
Defensively, the back five make it very

00:06:48.800 --> 00:06:50.479
difficult to break down with wing backs

00:06:50.479 --> 00:06:52.160
tucking in alongside the center backs.

00:06:52.160 --> 00:06:53.919
In attack, the wing backs provide width

00:06:53.919 --> 00:06:55.360
while the two strikers stay ready to

00:06:55.360 --> 00:06:57.039
counter quickly. It's a system often

00:06:57.039 --> 00:06:58.479
used by teams who want to defend deep

00:06:58.479 --> 00:07:00.080
and hit opponents on the break, but it

00:07:00.080 --> 00:07:01.759
still allows for a striking partnership.

00:07:01.759 --> 00:07:04.479
5-4-1. The 5-4-1 is one of the most

00:07:04.479 --> 00:07:06.240
defensive systems in football. It has

00:07:06.240 --> 00:07:08.319
five defenders, four midfielders, and a

00:07:08.319 --> 00:07:10.160
lone striker. Defensively, it's

00:07:10.160 --> 00:07:11.680
incredibly hard to break down with

00:07:11.680 --> 00:07:13.520
almost no space between the lines. The

00:07:13.520 --> 00:07:15.199
wide midfielders drop deep to help the

00:07:15.199 --> 00:07:16.880
fullbacks, forming a low block. In

00:07:16.880 --> 00:07:18.080
attack, it relies heavily on

00:07:18.080 --> 00:07:19.759
counterattacks with the lone striker

00:07:19.759 --> 00:07:21.440
supported by quick runs from midfield.

00:07:21.440 --> 00:07:23.199
It's most often used by underdogs trying

00:07:23.199 --> 00:07:25.199
to frustrate bigger teams, sacrificing

00:07:25.199 --> 00:07:26.479
attacking numbers for defensive

00:07:26.479 --> 00:07:28.160
strength. While not the most exciting,

00:07:28.160 --> 00:07:29.360
it's very effective in the right

00:07:29.360 --> 00:07:32.319
situations. 5-2-3. The 5-2-3 has five

00:07:32.319 --> 00:07:34.240
defenders, two central midfielders, and

00:07:34.240 --> 00:07:36.240
three attackers. Defensively, the wing

00:07:36.240 --> 00:07:38.000
backs tuck into a back five, while the

00:07:38.000 --> 00:07:39.680
two midfielders work hard to cover the

00:07:39.680 --> 00:07:41.599
center. In attack, the front three press

00:07:41.599 --> 00:07:43.520
high and break forward quickly with wing

00:07:43.520 --> 00:07:45.440
backs pushing on to create width. This

00:07:45.440 --> 00:07:46.880
shape is compact at the back but

00:07:46.880 --> 00:07:48.479
aggressive up front, making it useful

00:07:48.479 --> 00:07:50.240
for teams who want to defend solidly and

00:07:50.240 --> 00:07:52.000
then spring forward in numbers. It's a

00:07:52.000 --> 00:07:53.360
modern variation often used in

00:07:53.360 --> 00:07:54.720
international football when teams want

00:07:54.720 --> 00:07:56.479
both stability and counterattacking

00:07:56.479 --> 00:07:58.240
power. Thank you for watching and if you

00:07:58.240 --> 00:08:01.759
enjoyed this video, you will love this